        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 15 at 7:55PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 755 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Broad River Campground,
or 15 miles southeast of Elberton. This storm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Delhi, Floral Hill, and Danburg.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
